Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Thasian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay medium-fine light brown. Rectangular stamp with sculptor's drill(?) symbol.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
Curator's comments: Names Euryanax (Thasian fabricant) and Hippides (Thasian eponym). Garlan, Y., Les timbres amphoriques de Thasos. 1, Timbres protothasiens et thasiens anciens (Paris 1999), no. 903 [but not, as stated there, from Lesbos] Names, Euryanax, Ippides.
